Do you wash your hands?
Scientists have found that washing your hands ALSO CHANGES YOUR MOOD.
98 people, divided into three groups, took part in the experiment.
The first two had the task of solving an unsolvable task.
Of course, both failed.
But the group that washed their hands after failure appeared to be much more optimistic than the group that didn&#39;t wash their hands.
The group &quot;with washed hands&quot; also performed better than the other group in the next test.
Nevertheless, those who washed their hands achieved worse results in other tests than those who did not wash them.
The results of the &quot;washed&quot; were at the level of the third group, whose participants had not experienced any previous failure.
According to psychologists, the results of the test show that physical cleanliness removes really negative feelings after failure.
At the same time, however, motivation decreases, test takers have to concentrate much more in the next exams.
If we were to transfer the research results to the Czech Republic, we would probably be the most optimistic after returning from WC.
