Elsewhere, the hope is that a wary public will embrace the concept if the device can do more, not less.
In New York City, transportation officials are trying to develop a tolling device that would also be equipped to pay parking meter fees, provide mileage-based insurance and collect data on the speed of other drivers so motorists can avoid traffic jams .
