This displaces unwanted air.
The last trampled layer of cabbage is covered with a sheet and weighed down with water.
&quot;The cabbage crumb then ripens for six to eight weeks under spontaneous lactic fermentation without any addition of fermentation-promoting substances,&quot; emphasized director Kladroba.
The natural process corresponds to production in domestic conditions, the individual layers are sprinkled with salt and cumin.
After fermentation, the cabbage goes to the filling line.
It is packed in a sweet and sour pickle in bags or jars and subjected to sterilization.
Hamé supplies sauerkraut mainly to the domestic and Slovak markets.
