I see more lonely exercisers, each in their own tornado of anxiety.
Writing books saved me.
I am participating in that vast, millennia-long movement of the life system on this planet - that birth of an elusive future.
That immense, breathtaking complexity of life, where every stone is a direct heir of our presence.
We are the players of a sad and beautiful game where, through trial and error, another and another generation of beings is created, which in trillions of interactions per second creates some kind of superhuman, artificial intelligence.
Twelve years is a relatively long time.
Do you see your writing as an ongoing process, or did you start completely from scratch?
The soliloquy, or better said the dialogue between the right and left halves of the brain, sometimes surfaces and takes the form of a book.
As periods of peace are interwoven with quietly sleeping metastases of wars that may one day awaken - so my book is twelve years of silence dressed in words.
I could feel the silent avalanche of life growing in my brain, and if I didn&#39;t do something, it would one day silently overwhelm me.
It is a set of questions formulated by the brain and put to the layers that are stored in the darkness &quot;below the surface of consciousness&quot;.
The neocortex, the gray cerebral cortex, questions older evolutionary formations, goes to the ancient tree rings of the brain.
He speaks to furry beasts, asks snakes, looks for an answer in the flight of birds, raises his eyes to the clouds in the sky.
Yes, the moral law within me and the starry sky above me.
