A gap appears in the previously functional mechanisms of our thinking, feeling and behavior.
Here it is good to quote Nietzsche: &quot;He gazed into the abyss for so long that the abyss gazed into him.&quot;
A genuine feeling - that a person is lost, if all hope disappears, he psychologically &quot;dies&quot; and a new quality begins.
And why do I care personally?
I will answer with a parable.
Once upon a time, one fell into a pool and drowned, days, months and years went by, he kept drowning while reading, and those books taught him to swim - that is, to live.
