The project should last until 2016.
The authors were inspired by their neighbors.
This mechanism has been successfully applied for several years in Slovakia, where the problem with socially excluded localities is incomparably higher than in the Czech Republic.
&quot;There are so-called Roma settlements,&quot; the authors of the report said.
It is not yet clear how many specialists there should be in the Czech Republic.
The answer is to be given by an analysis that will determine the places where a special police officer would be needed.
