&quot;I will gladly and with all responsibility try to promote those steps that can improve the position of nurses.&quot;
&quot;We have excellent and skilled nurses in our healthcare sector, but I would also like to appeal to those colleagues who do not help us much with their approach to patients, to perform their profession with all empathy and help us improve the image of nurses in the eyes of the public,&quot; says Alena Šmídová.
The newly appointed Head Nurse for the Czech Republic, Alena Šmídová, also stated on the occasion of her inauguration that she wants to deal with various aspects of the nurse&#39;s job position and intends to cooperate with professional associations, professional societies, educators, other non-medical professions and doctors.
&quot;Fundamentally, I do not want to separate the professions of doctors and nurses, but on the contrary, I see them standing side by side, while each has their own competences and, together with other health workers, they form a coordinated work team that provides health services for the benefit of the patient.&quot;
&quot;I myself encounter a number of problems that occur when performing the profession of nurses, I perceive these difficulties and I intend to participate in their solution.&quot;
These include, for example, ensuring the simplification of nursing and medical documentation.
&quot;I know from my own experience that some administrative tasks unnecessarily burden nurses and take away their time, which they could and should rather devote to patients,&quot; says Alena Šmídová.
Other areas on which he intends to focus include improving working conditions, finding ways to improve mutual cooperation in the team and with the management of health service providers, adjusting competencies and also labor law issues, such as compliance with the labor code or not overburdening nurses with their insufficient number at a given time and place.
We often hear anonymous complaints, but for fear of possible punishment, they are not documented in a specific case where the rules could be violated.
&quot;Where there is no prosecutor, there is no judge, so the function of the Chief Nurse of the CR could in this case serve as a guarantee of preserving the anonymity of such a complaint and let the relevant authorities examine the specific case,&quot; concludes Alena Šmídová.
M.Sc. Alena Šmídová graduated from the Secondary School of Nursing in the field of Nursing (graduated in 1978) and the Faculty of Philosophy of the Charles University in Prague in the study program Nursing - Pedagogy (graduated in 1992).
Since 2010, he has been working as the head of the department of nursing and other non-medical fields and recognition of qualifications at the Department of Education and Science of the Ministry of Health.
In the course of her professional career, she worked as a bedside nurse in the internal department, and also worked as a teacher at the Secondary Medical School, where she was the statutory deputy director for 8 years.
